THE South African Weather Services has warned that it&rsquo;s going to be a wet weekend ahead. It advised that there&rsquo;s a 60% chance of rain every day this week until Saturday.Skies are expected to clear from Sunday.Forecaster Lulama Pheme said there would be severe thunderstorms in Gauteng, KZN, North West, Mpumalanga and the Free State.She added people living in lower areas are at risk of possible flash floods.Meanwhile, the Joburg Emergency Management Services has warned residents to stay away from low-lying areas. &ldquo;Our team will be on high alert in different areas and roads where flooding is possible. We are asking parents to advise their children not to play near storm drainage areas. &ldquo;Children must not play in the water during this time and parents are advised to keep their children indoors,&rdquo; it said.Joburg Roads Agency spokeswoman Bertha Peter-Scheepers warned people that flash floods could occur within minutes or hours of excessive rainfall.She said: &ldquo;Do not dump things in drainage systems that could block the drains and cause &shy;flooding.&rdquo;